zation? What about the FipsOperationError class — maybe that’s not right? A new report shows none after attempts, possibly because they ran without our previous modifications. Since modifications exist in this session, I definitely need to refine my approach, especially since regular FipsStatus might not cover the checksum correctly.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Implementing isolated classloader tests**\\n\\nI'm thinking about implementing an isolated classloader test in NativeLoaderTest. I’m considering borrowing the classloader and wanting to avoid direct reflection. It seems like using the public FipsStatus API could allow for dynamic library loading, but I’ll need to catch unsupported errors. \\n\\nThere’s a question about whether both methods can coexist and what approach to take with test methods' ordering too. Oh, and I need to ensure the system property doesn’t cause issues during builds. It’s quite a task!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Analyzing FipsStatus behavior**\\n\\nI'm figuring out if a direct call to FipsStatus might cause a checksum failure, setting the static statusException and interfering with system-loaded classes. Isolating tests could help, but I need to ensure that the isolated tests run first. It seems that direct access can also set the FipsStatus statusException if a failure occurs. I'll need to manage imports carefully and check how the classloader loads specific classes. Let's also look into handling exceptions properly, especially around the statusClass invocation. This is getting a bit intricate!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Troubleshooting test resources**\\n\\nI see that the test resource should return a close function and verify that forcedVariant isn't null. If there's a selected variant, it has to be checked. The variantPath leads to /native/linux/x86_64/coverage_missing_variant, and I need to ensure that installLib properly calls loadVariantsDeps to pull in the necessary dependencies. But it seems that when I try to parse these resources, I’m getting an empty result. This is all quite puzzling and I need to dig deeper!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering test resources**\\n\\nI’m thinking about the potential issues with test resources being added to the test classpath after the dependency jar. When I use `resourceLoader.getResource(\\\"native/...\\\")`, it searches the classpath in order, so it seems our resource is found, which is good! However, I wonder if we could avoid having direct test resources hidden in `src/test/resources/META-INF`. It’s allowed not to include the native-image config, so perhaps I’ll need to make some edits.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_CzjenPwlEfu5275gXbmGT6Dv|fc_0674e00c56c31857016a3f788529208197b78785c56247f00b", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.bouncycastle/bc-fips/2.1.2/src/test/java/org_bouncycastle/bc_fips/NativeLoaderTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "import static org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.assertTrue;\n\nimport java.nio.file.Path;\n\nimport org.bouncycastle.crypto.CryptoServicesRegistrar;\n", "newText": "import static org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.assertTrue;\n\nimport java.io.IOException;\nimport java.io.InputStream;\nimport java.lang.reflect.InvocationTargetException;\nimport java.net.URL;\nimport java.net.URLConnection;\nimport java.net.URLStreamHandler;\nimport java.nio.file.Path;\nimport java.security.AllPermission;\nimport java.security.CodeSource;\nimport java.security.PermissionCollection;\nimport java.security.Permissions;\nimport java.security.ProtectionDomain;\n\nimport org.bouncycastle.crypto.CryptoServicesRegistrar;\n"}, {"oldText": "import org.bouncycastle.crypto.fips.FipsStatus;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.AfterAll;\n", "newText": "import org.bouncycastle.crypto.fips.FipsStatus;\nimport org.graalvm.internal.tck.NativeImageSupport;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.AfterAll;\n"}, {"oldText": "import org.junit.jupiter.api.Order;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.io.TempDir;\n\n@Order(0)\npublic class NativeLoaderTest {\n", "newText": "import org.junit.jupiter.api.MethodOrderer;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Order;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.TestMethodOrder;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.io.TempDir;\n\n@Order(0)\n@TestMethodOrder(MethodOrderer.OrderAnnotation.class)\npublic class NativeLoaderTest {\n"}, {"oldText": "    private static final String NATIVE_INSTALL_DIR_PROPERTY = \"org.bouncycastle.native.loader.install_dir\";\n    private static final String MISSING_NATIVE_VARIANT = \"coverage_missing_variant\";\n\n", "newText": "    private static final String NATIVE_INSTALL_DIR_PROPERTY = \"org.bouncycastle.native.loader.install_dir\";\n    private static final String MISSING_NATIVE_VARIANT = \"coverage_missing_variant\";\n    private static final String FIPS_STATUS_CLASS_NAME = \"org.bouncycastle.crypto.fips.FipsStatus\";\n    private static final String MARKER_RESOURCE_NAME = \"org/bouncycastle/MARKER\";\n\n"}, {"oldText": "    @Test\n    void fipsStartupAttemptsNativeProbeAndVariantDependencyResourceLookup() {\n", "newText": "    @Test\n    @Order(1)\n    void isolatedFipsStartupAttemptsNativeProbeAndVariantDependencyResourceLookup() throws Exception {\n        try {\n            CodeSource codeSource = FipsStatus.class.getProtectionDomain().getCodeSource();\n            NativeResourceClassLoader classLoader = new NativeResourceClassLoader(\n                    NativeLoaderTest.class.getClassLoader(), codeSource);\n            Class<?> statusClass = classLoader.loadClass(FIPS_STATUS_CLASS_NAME);\n\n            assertTrue((Boolean)statusClass.getMethod(\"isReady\").invoke(null));\n        } catch (ClassNotFoundException exception) {\n            assertTrue(FipsStatus.isReady());\n        } catch (InvocationTargetException exception) {\n            handleInvocationFailure(exception);\n        } catch (Error error) {\n            if (!NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(error)) {\n                throw error;\n            }\n        }\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    @Order(2)\n    void fipsStartupAttemptsNativeProbeAndVariantDependencyResourceLookup() {\n"}, {"oldText": "    private static void restoreProperty(String propertyName, String previousValue) {\n", "newText": "    private static void handleInvocationFailure(InvocationTargetException exception) throws Exception {\n        Throwable cause = exception.getCause();\n        if (cause instanceof Error error) {\n            if (isChecksumFailure(error) || NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(error)) {\n                return;\n            }\n            throw error;\n        }\n        if (cause instanceof Exception checkedException) {\n            throw checkedException;\n        }\n        throw exception;\n    }\n\n    private static void restoreProperty(String propertyName, String previousValue) {\n"}, {"oldText": "    private static boolean isChecksumFailure(Error error) {\n        return \"org.bouncycastle.crypto.fips.FipsOperationError\".equals(error.getClass().getName())\n                && error.getMessage() != null\n                && error.getMessage().startsWith(\"Module checksum failed\");\n    }\n}\n", "newText": "    private static boolean isChecksumFailure(Error error) {\n        return \"org.bouncycastle.crypto.fips.FipsOperationError\".equals(error.getClass().getName())\n                && error.getMessage() != null\n                && error.getMessage().startsWith(\"Module checksum failed\");\n    }\n\n    private static final class NativeResourceClassLoader extends ClassLoader {\n        private static final String LICENSE_CLASS_NAME = \"org.bouncycastle.LICENSE\";\n\n        private final ClassLoader resourceLoader;\n        private final ProtectionDomain bouncyCastleDomain;\n        private final ProtectionDomain markerFallbackDomain;\n\n        NativeResourceClassLoader(ClassLoader resourceLoader, CodeSource codeSource) {\n            super(null);\n            this.resourceLoader = resourceLoader;\n            this.bouncyCastleDomain = new ProtectionDomain(codeSource, allPermissions());\n            this.markerFallbackDomain = new ProtectionDomain(null, allPermissions());\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        protected Class<?> loadClass(String name, boolean resolve) throws ClassNotFoundException {\n            synchronized (getClassLoadingLock(name)) {\n                Class<?> loadedClass = findLoadedClass(name);\n                if (loadedClass == null) {\n                    loadedClass = loadClassFromBouncyCastleJar(name);\n                }\n                if (loadedClass == null) {\n                    loadedClass = ClassLoader.getPlatformClassLoader().loadClass(name);\n                }\n                if (resolve) {\n                    resolveClass(loadedClass);\n                }\n                return loadedClass;\n            }\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public URL getResource(String name) {\n            if (MARKER_RESOURCE_NAME.equals(name)) {\n                return markerUrl();\n            }\n            return resourceLoader.getResource(name);\n        }\n\n        private Class<?> loadClassFromBouncyCastleJar(String name) throws ClassNotFoundException {\n            if (!name.startsWith(\"org.bouncycastle.\")) {\n                return null;\n            }\n            return findClass(name);\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        protected Class<?> findClass(String name) throws ClassNotFoundException {\n            String resourceName = name.replace('.', '/') + \".class\";\n            try (InputStream input = resourceLoader.getResourceAsStream(resourceName)) {\n                if (input == null) {\n                    throw new ClassNotFoundException(name);\n                }\n                byte[] bytecode = input.readAllBytes();\n                return defineClass(name, bytecode, 0, bytecode.length, protectionDomain(name));\n            } catch (IOException exception) {\n                throw new ClassNotFoundException(name, exception);\n            }\n        }\n\n        private ProtectionDomain protectionDomain(String className) {\n            if (LICENSE_CLASS_NAME.equals(className)) {\n                return markerFallbackDomain;\n            }\n            return bouncyCastleDomain;\n        }\n\n        private static PermissionCollection allPermissions() {\n            Permissions permissions = new Permissions();\n            permissions.add(new AllPermission());\n            permissions.setReadOnly();\n            return permissions;\n        }\n\n        private URL markerUrl() {\n            try {\n                return new URL(null, \"vfs:/bc-fips/MARKER\", new URLStreamHandler() {\n                    @Override\n                    protected URLConnection openConnection(URL url) throws IOException {\n                        throw new IOException(\"marker URL is only used for its external form\");\n                    }\n                });\n            } catch (IOException exception) {\n                throw new IllegalStateException(exception);\n            }\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1277, "output": 3110, "cacheRead": 65024, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 69411, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1782544492467, "responseId": "resp_0674e00c56c31857016a3f786d14588197beaac31e88f967fc"}}
