": "Refined the `NativeLoader` coverage test to avoid the checksum path blocking native-loader execution.\n\nUpdated:\n- `tests/src/org.bouncycastle/bc-fips/2.1.2/src/test/java/org_bouncycastle/bc_fips/NativeLoaderTest.java`\n\nKept/added test resources used to drive the native resource lookup path:\n- `tests/src/org.bouncycastle/bc-fips/2.1.2/src/test/resources/native/linux/x86_64/probe/libbc-probe.so`\n- `tests/src/org.bouncycastle/bc-fips/2.1.2/src/test/resources/native/linux/x86_64/deps.list`\n\nKey refinement:\n- Added an isolated Bouncy Castle class loader modeled on the existing FIPS status test pattern.\n- The isolated loader gives `org.bouncycastle.LICENSE` a null `CodeSource`, forcing the marker fallback path and avoiding module checksum failure before `NativeLoader.loadDriver()` runs.\n- The test now verifies the forced native variant is selected via the public `CryptoServicesRegistrar.getNativeServices().getVariant()` API, proving execution reached beyond the early `\"java\"` variant branch.\n- The provided fake probe resource lets `NativeLoader.loadDriver()` reach its `Class#getResourceAsStream(...)` probe lookup.\n- The provided `deps.list` resource lets the missing forced variant path reach `NativeLoader.getFile(...)`.\n- Dynamic class loading is wrapped with the required Native Image unsupported-feature handling.\n\nI did not run tests, per instruction.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0674e00c56c31857016a3f78d96df0819787253e646bf4a61c\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 678, "output": 2042, "cacheRead": 74752, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 77472, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782544575910, "responseId": "resp_0674e00c56c31857016a3f78c0822c819799698fbd85a8d59e"}}
[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating native image settings**\n\nIt seems I’m considering the implications of changing `NATIVE_CPU_VARIANT` to missing. This could lead to the FipsStatus native loader trying to access resources during runtime. I wonder if the `Class#getResourceAsStream` call would be impacted, particularly its coverage in the native image. It’s possible that during nativeTest execution, the Native Image might not include a fake resource unless a resource-config is generated. There’s quite a bit to think through here!\n\n**Considering resource activation**\n\nI'm thinking that it could be beneficial to focus on NativeLoader. However, it seems like the resource might not be activated for the class. I'm realizing that this is part of a test setup, which makes me wonder if there's anything else I need to address or adjust. Let me figure this out to make sure everything is in the right place! It's always good to double-check these details.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0674e00c56c31857016a3f78c16ac88197afe7840646a418a2\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqP3jZ11PNJp3GK4JwWFZCAtAVWIsrSiJlRGCPCA2WEq2IQQgXavu3jJeFMvG2ooWN9cAtV8Wv21CxMHz7gaDpWOnPnugCdg-dZndSiTkbRwJTe1mdO4SqhCLcsoDEDSDlGF-8qT7cUm4VgAZuMVdAFagm62DoxVohZhKNKA2feKh1juJxAAksRGvyBmU9VkXq12Ci3YvXVfHNhHv3z12_cUqIvCh0QlSx1etOksul8pAi22p6Yokjn3bQ1XCdrsj3DihJRMkufnFvhXVtNbI0eDI7VESqDRPT2NHNhYQOY1AqQewQtPqSF31tmd-Cje4goaXQJkDRL7z6Upe3Lj6Mp2BlWnxQ1jtEbViTGU2H-HNxyGGweSo-XTOHNoZ4w-RNXc6utdoBL4dNEMDel_MjmvWL_LOxtT7-SvkVc0ec0mWZZ1mIjyq-S12CVZpAYgTM4WHyxhldwy2G_v3Jo7UOVjkVrLLe5QbvY35v6Rk8GyNo5i54UhY04my7Rt7Niip-MQ24MiTcEHfQIVA7ZS4JfM08qJKro7mVfhHC_DUwM865VX4arbMTyJzEvCmEgUnlcdSLRprx73fHof84KnulkiJbHtQ7ZHi8mbW9vGpqs6pyRSOtFvTyuEd0nb8bxL8D3YDG1ubRSz1V8Ye1hLH8CKP2zhUhCpLsexvuZakM9Vp6IHixZ0vUiNbYHM-lnnuzhr3xXXRMgePlGYee3Eu-6U6FB4X8mU29q4JeNFEDkPPGgjXk2QUtu7G-RywCruQXMMEyDEpa81MSv-ldcBrQMdqVY